The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Boys were in fine touch: Manoranjan
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Boys were in fine touch: Manoranjan
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Coach Manoranjan Bhattacharjee feels that East Bengals 3-1 drubbing of Peerless will boost their chances in Tuesdays derby against arch-rivals Mohun Bagan.         
	Yeah this is obviously a good result for us, Bhattacharjee said after the match.         
	The players were confident and thats a good sign when you are heading for a big match within a couple of days. They appeared in fine touch and this will help us on that big day, he added.         
	He however, was unhappy with the ground conditions.         
	Its quite risky for players playing on such conditions. Theres always a chance of getting injured and this also affects performance, Bhattacharjee stated.         
	Meanwhile, Peerless coach, Mihir Bose alleged East Bengals second goal was scored from an off-side. It was a clear off-side Everybody witnessed it other than the referee, Bose argued.                                                                                                                          
